values:
There's a bit from the West Wing that came to mind today.

&quot;If they're shooting at you, you must be doing something right.&quot;

All the GOP camp can do is attack the other guy.  Criticize his patriotism because he wants to end a war, use his middle name as an epithet, try to make people afraid of him.&nbsp; 

You know who I'm afraid of?&nbsp; People who accuse Barack Obama of being a terrorist to score points.&nbsp; People who are willing to skim the bottom instead of raising the level of discourse.

&quot;That One?&quot;&nbsp; Seriously?&nbsp; &quot;That One?&quot;&nbsp; Do you really have nothing else to offer?

So if McCain's campaign manager has been on the payroll of Freddie Mac (getting paid $15,000 a month from 2005 until LAST MONTH) and the Treasury Department has now taken de facto ownership of Freddie Mac, and I as a taxpaying citizen have paid for the government to do this, I have a question...

Does Rick Davis work for me?

&quot;Rick, step into my office.&quot;
&quot;Why?&quot;
&quot;Cause you fucking fired!&quot;
